        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/67e7ee/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2021-12-06T20:43:32.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I saw this also, but it is not exactly clear what changes lmlb has actually made in the wine production. It is difficult to believe he just walked in with those sexy orange pants and POOF, the wine turns into a high value premier Cru. Interesting things are going on in Pommard however, seems lot of producers are upping their game in an effort to raise the profile (and prices of course). Interesting and a bit tempting. This is the kind of detailed information I would like to get from someone who is on the ground in Burgundy. Perhaps who is working in a major wine publication. Perhaps someone with a British accent. And initials starting with a W\u2026</p>",
